node.text: @alisoneroman knew the internet would yell at her about the Thousand Island Dressing. But she is a bold and brave woman who doesn't want a mixture of mayo + ketchup on her crunchy, citrusy seafood salad, so here we are. If you make this, you won't be mad about it. Get the recipe here: https://nyti.ms/2WWluna (Video: @scottloitsch @vaughn)

node.text: BEHOLD: 🥒 Pickle upside-down cake. 🥒 That’s right, on this week’s episode of Mystery Menu, the secret ingredient is pickles. Click the link in bio to see how @sohlae and @hamegram do it.

node.text: 🚨 Quick and easy one-pot meal alert! 🚨 Get @samanthaseneviratne's recipe for Coconut Rice With Shrimp and Corn at the link in bio. (Photo: @bryangardnerphotography, food styling: @lishsteiling)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and food.

node.text: According to one of our commenters, @alexaweibel's Kale Salad With Peaches and Cornbread Croutons "is so good it tastes like dessert!" Yes! Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @_joelgoldberg, food styling: @bwashbu, prop styling: @paigehicksnyc)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 10, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: @ottolenghi's Lemon-Labneh Possets With Meringue and Burnt Lemon Powder turn simple ingredients into something very special. Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @chrisrsimpson, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and food.

node.text: For @david_tanis's Crispy Chicken Thighs With Peppers, Capers and Olives, you make that crispy, burnished skin by cooking the chicken with a weighted pan on top. Fun! Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @dmalosh, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 09, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Chunky jams and fruit jellies bursting with flavor can turn simple breakfast toast into a celebration. 🥳  At the link in bio, @yewande_komolafe shows you how.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 09, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Serve @clarkbar's Buttery Scallops With Lemon and Herbs over a big pile of buttered noodles and you've got yourself very a nice-looking meal. Get the recipe at the link in bio! (Photo: @chrisrsimpson, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 09, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: ☀️ Good ☀️ morning ☀️ to @yossyarefi's Plum and Raspberry Cornmeal Crisp. Get the recipe at the link in bio! (Photo: @bryangardnerphotography, food styling: @bwashbu)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on September 08, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: "Great for tired weekdays when you want a satisfying meal in less than an hour." Sounds like @clarkbar's recipe for Sheet-Pan Chicken With Zucchini and Basil will definitely be coming in handy. Get it at the link in bio. (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @judy.kim)

node.text: 🍳🍚✨ Read more from @ericjoonho at the link in bio.

node.text: There's a special kind of magic that happens when very ripe plantains are cooked in high heat, as they are for these fritters. In @yewande_komolafe's recipe for Mosa, the plantain sugars caramelize, making each bite pleasantly sweet. ✨ Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @hadassmirnoff)
